---
/**
 * Cancellation Policy Page (T150)
 *
 * Comprehensive cancellation policy for courses, events, subscriptions, and services.
 * Last Updated: November 6, 2025
 */

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'November 6, 2025';
const effectiveDate = 'November 6, 2025';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cancellation Policy"
  description="Learn about our cancellation policies for courses, events, and subscriptions. Understand the procedures, timelines, and what happens when you cancel."
  keywords="cancellation policy, cancel course, cancel event, cancel subscription, spirituality platform"
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-lg py-2xl max-w-4xl">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-2xl text-center">
      <h1 class="mb-md text-4xl font-bold text-text">Cancellation Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-text-light">
        Last Updated: <time datetime={effectiveDate}>{lastUpdated}</time>
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section class="mb-2xl rounded-xl bg-surface p-xl">
      <p class="mb-md text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-light">
        At Spirituality Platform, we understand that plans change. This Cancellation Policy explains how to cancel courses, events, subscriptions, and other services, along with the associated timelines and procedures.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-light">
        For information about refunds related to cancellations, please see our <a href="/refund-policy" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">Refund Policy</a>. This policy focuses on the cancellation procedures and what happens to your account and access.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Table of Contents -->
    <nav class="mb-2xl rounded-xl bg-background p-lg" aria-label="Table of Contents">
      <h2 class="mb-md text-xl font-bold text-text">Table of Contents</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-xs text-text-light">
        <li><a href="#course-cancellation" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">1. Course Enrollment Cancellation</a></li>
        <li><a href="#event-cancellation" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">2. Event Booking Cancellation</a></li>
        <li><a href="#subscription-cancellation" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">3. Subscription Cancellation</a></li>
        <li><a href="#account-cancellation" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">4. Account Closure</a></li>
        <li><a href="#how-to-cancel" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">5. How to Cancel</a></li>
        <li><a href="#after-cancellation" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">6. What Happens After Cancellation</a></li>
        <li><a href="#reinstatement" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">7. Reinstatement</a></li>
        <li><a href="#we-cancel" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">8. When We Cancel</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contact" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">9. Contact Information</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <section id="course-cancellation" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">1. Course Enrollment Cancellation</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1.1 When You Can Cancel</h3>
          <p>
            You can cancel a course enrollment at any time, but refund eligibility depends on timing and progress:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Within 30 days + less than 90% complete:</strong> Full refund available</li>
            <li><strong>After 30 days or more than 90% complete:</strong> No refund, but you retain access</li>
            <li><strong>Before starting:</strong> Full refund, no questions asked</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1.2 Cancellation Process</h3>
          <p>
            To cancel a course enrollment:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Log in to your account at <a href="/account" class="text-primary hover:underline">spiritualityplatform.com/account</a></li>
            <li>Go to "My Courses" section</li>
            <li>Find the course you want to cancel</li>
            <li>Click "Cancel Enrollment" or "Request Refund"</li>
            <li>Confirm your cancellation</li>
            <li>You'll receive an email confirmation within minutes</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1.3 What Happens to Your Progress</h3>
          <p>
            When you cancel a course:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>If requesting refund:</strong> Access ends immediately, progress deleted after 30 days</li>
            <li><strong>If keeping access:</strong> Your progress is saved, you can continue learning</li>
            <li><strong>Certificates:</strong> Completion certificates are revoked if you receive a refund</li>
            <li><strong>Notes and bookmarks:</strong> Saved if you keep access, deleted if refunded</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1.4 Course Bundle Cancellations</h3>
          <p>
            For course bundles:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>You can cancel the entire bundle within 30 days for full refund</li>
            <li>Individual course cancellations within bundles are calculated at individual prices</li>
            <li>If you complete any course beyond 90%, the bundle becomes non-refundable</li>
            <li>You can cancel access to specific courses while keeping others</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1.5 Pre-Orders and Upcoming Courses</h3>
          <p>
            For courses that haven't started yet:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Full refund available anytime before course launch</li>
            <li>Automatic refund if course is cancelled or significantly delayed</li>
            <li>You'll be notified by email if course dates change</li>
            <li>30-day refund period starts from actual course launch date</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <section id="event-cancellation" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">2. Event Booking Cancellation</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2.1 Cancellation Deadlines</h3>
          <p>
            Event cancellations must be made according to these timelines:
          </p>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-lg my-md">
            <table class="w-full">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/20">
                  <th class="py-sm px-md text-left text-text">Notice Period</th>
                  <th class="py-sm px-md text-left text-text">Refund</th>
                  <th class="py-sm px-md text-left text-text">Status</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-text-light">
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">30+ days before</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">100%</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md text-success font-medium">Easy cancel</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">15-30 days before</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">75%</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md text-success font-medium">Standard cancel</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">7-14 days before</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">50%</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md text-warning font-medium">Late cancel</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">3-6 days before</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">25%</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md text-warning font-medium">Very late cancel</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Less than 3 days</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">50% credit</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md text-error font-medium">No refund, credit only</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2.2 How to Cancel Event Bookings</h3>
          <p>
            To cancel an event booking:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Log in to your account</li>
            <li>Navigate to "My Events" or "Upcoming Events"</li>
            <li>Find the event you want to cancel</li>
            <li>Click "Cancel Booking"</li>
            <li>Review the refund amount (based on timeline)</li>
            <li>Confirm cancellation</li>
            <li>Receive immediate email confirmation</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2.3 Group Bookings</h3>
          <p>
            For group event registrations:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Full group cancellation:</strong> Standard timeline applies to entire group</li>
            <li><strong>Individual cancellation:</strong> Individual participants can cancel based on timeline</li>
            <li><strong>Group organizer:</strong> The person who booked can cancel anyone in the group</li>
            <li><strong>Refund distribution:</strong> Refunds go to the original payment method</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2.4 Transferring Event Registrations</h3>
          <p>
            Instead of cancelling, you can transfer your registration:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Transfer to another person:</strong> No fee, must be done 7+ days before event</li>
            <li><strong>Transfer to different event:</strong> Pay any price difference, $25 admin fee</li>
            <li><strong>Transfer to future date:</strong> Same event at later date, no fee if available</li>
            <li><strong>How to transfer:</strong> Contact support with transfer details</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2.5 Wait-Listed Events</h3>
          <p>
            For events where you're on a waiting list:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>You can cancel wait-list position anytime with full refund</li>
            <li>If you're moved from wait-list to confirmed, standard policy applies</li>
            <li>You'll have 24 hours to cancel after confirmation for full refund</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <section id="subscription-cancellation" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">3. Subscription Cancellation</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3.1 When You Can Cancel</h3>
          <p>
            You can cancel your subscription at any time:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Anytime:</strong> No penalty for early cancellation</li>
            <li><strong>No commitment:</strong> No long-term contract required</li>
            <li><strong>Keep access:</strong> Access continues until end of current billing period</li>
            <li><strong>No partial refunds:</strong> No refunds for unused days in current period</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3.2 How to Cancel Subscription</h3>
          <p>
            To cancel your subscription:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Log in to your account</li>
            <li>Go to "Account Settings" → "Subscription"</li>
            <li>Click "Cancel Subscription"</li>
            <li>Select reason for cancellation (optional, helps us improve)</li>
            <li>Confirm cancellation</li>
            <li>You'll see confirmation on screen and via email</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3.3 Subscription Types</h3>

          <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-lg my-md">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-text mb-sm">Monthly Subscriptions</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs mb-md">
              <li>Cancel anytime, access until end of current month</li>
              <li>No charge for next month if cancelled before renewal</li>
              <li>Can reactivate anytime (may require new signup)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 class="font-semibold text-text mb-sm">Annual Subscriptions</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs mb-md">
              <li>Cancel anytime, access until end of current year</li>
              <li>No prorated refund for remaining months</li>
              <li>Will not auto-renew after current period ends</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 class="font-semibold text-text mb-sm">Trial Periods</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
              <li>Cancel during trial = no charge, no commitment</li>
              <li>Cancel before trial ends to avoid being charged</li>
              <li>Set calendar reminder for trial end date</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3.4 Pause Subscription (Alternative)</h3>
          <p>
            Instead of cancelling, you can pause:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Pause for 1-6 months</li>
            <li><strong>No charges:</strong> No billing during pause period</li>
            <li><strong>Keep settings:</strong> Preferences and history maintained</li>
            <li><strong>Auto-resume:</strong> Automatically resumes after pause period (or cancel permanently)</li>
            <li><strong>How to pause:</strong> Account Settings → Subscription → Pause Subscription</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3.5 Failed Payment Cancellations</h3>
          <p>
            If your payment fails:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>We'll retry payment 3 times over 7 days</li>
            <li>You'll receive email reminders to update payment</li>
            <li>After 3 failed attempts, subscription automatically cancels</li>
            <li>You'll have 30 days to reinstate before data deletion</li>
            <li>Update payment method in Account Settings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <section id="account-cancellation" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">4. Account Closure</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4.1 Closing Your Account</h3>
          <p>
            You can permanently close your account at any time:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Permanent action:</strong> Cannot be undone after 30-day grace period</li>
            <li><strong>Access lost:</strong> Lose access to all purchased courses and content</li>
            <li><strong>Data deletion:</strong> Personal data deleted per GDPR/CCPA (see Privacy Policy)</li>
            <li><strong>No refunds:</strong> Past purchases are not refunded upon account closure</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4.2 Before You Close Your Account</h3>
          <p>
            Important things to do first:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Download certificates:</strong> Save any completion certificates</li>
            <li><strong>Export data:</strong> Download your personal data if desired</li>
            <li><strong>Cancel subscriptions:</strong> Ensure no recurring charges</li>
            <li><strong>Transfer ownership:</strong> For group purchases, transfer to another admin</li>
            <li><strong>Use credits:</strong> Any account credits will be forfeited</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4.3 How to Close Account</h3>
          <p>
            To permanently close your account:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Log in to your account</li>
            <li>Go to "Account Settings" → "Privacy & Security"</li>
            <li>Scroll to "Account Closure"</li>
            <li>Click "Close Account"</li>
            <li>Verify your identity (password or 2FA)</li>
            <li>Confirm you understand data will be deleted</li>
            <li>Select reason for closure (optional)</li>
            <li>Final confirmation: "Yes, close my account"</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4.4 Grace Period</h3>
          <p>
            After requesting account closure:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>30-day grace period:</strong> Account marked for deletion but not deleted yet</li>
            <li><strong>Can reactivate:</strong> Log in within 30 days to cancel closure request</li>
            <li><strong>No access:</strong> Cannot access courses or content during grace period</li>
            <li><strong>After 30 days:</strong> Account and data permanently deleted</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4.5 Temporary Deactivation (Alternative)</h3>
          <p>
            If you're not ready for permanent deletion:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Deactivate account:</strong> Temporarily disable without deletion</li>
            <li><strong>Keep purchases:</strong> All purchased content saved</li>
            <li><strong>Reactivate anytime:</strong> Simply log in to reactivate</li>
            <li><strong>No time limit:</strong> Can stay deactivated indefinitely</li>
            <li><strong>How to:</strong> Account Settings → Deactivate Account</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <section id="how-to-cancel" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">5. How to Cancel</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5.1 Self-Service Cancellation</h3>
          <p>
            Most cancellations can be done instantly through your account:
          </p>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-lg my-md">
            <p class="font-semibold text-text mb-sm">Step-by-Step:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-lg space-y-xs">
              <li>Log in at <a href="/login" class="text-primary hover:underline">spiritualityplatform.com/login</a></li>
              <li>Go to your dashboard</li>
              <li>Find the item you want to cancel (course, event, subscription)</li>
              <li>Click "Cancel" or "Request Refund"</li>
              <li>Follow the prompts</li>
              <li>Receive instant confirmation</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5.2 Email Cancellation</h3>
          <p>
            You can also cancel by email:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:cancel@spiritualityplatform.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">cancel@spiritualityplatform.com</a></li>
            <li><strong>Include:</strong> Account email, what you want to cancel, order/booking number</li>
            <li><strong>Response time:</strong> Processed within 1 business day</li>
            <li><strong>Confirmation:</strong> You'll receive email confirmation when processed</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5.3 Phone Cancellation</h3>
          <p>
            For immediate assistance with cancellations:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Phone:</strong> 1-800-SPIRIT-1 (1-800-774-7481)</li>
            <li><strong>Hours:</strong> Monday-Friday, 9 AM - 6 PM EST</li>
            <li><strong>Identity verification:</strong> Have your account email and order number ready</li>
            <li><strong>Instant processing:</strong> Cancellation processed while on the call</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5.4 Bulk Cancellations</h3>
          <p>
            If you need to cancel multiple items:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Contact support for assistance with bulk cancellations</li>
            <li>Provide list of order numbers or booking IDs</li>
            <li>We'll process all cancellations and confirm via single email</li>
            <li>Useful for group organizers or corporate accounts</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5.5 Third-Party Cancellations</h3>
          <p>
            If you purchased through a third party:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>Contact the original seller for cancellation</li>
            <li>Different cancellation policies may apply</li>
            <li>We cannot process refunds for third-party purchases</li>
            <li>Access keys can be deactivated upon request from seller</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <section id="after-cancellation" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">6. What Happens After Cancellation</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6.1 Immediate Effects</h3>
          <p>
            When you cancel:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Confirmation email:</strong> Instant confirmation of cancellation</li>
            <li><strong>Dashboard update:</strong> Status changes immediately</li>
            <li><strong>Auto-renewal:</strong> Subscriptions marked as "will not renew"</li>
            <li><strong>Calendar:</strong> Events removed from your event calendar</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6.2 Access Timeline</h3>
          <p>
            When your access ends:
          </p>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-lg my-md">
            <table class="w-full">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/20">
                  <th class="py-sm px-md text-left text-text">Item Type</th>
                  <th class="py-sm px-md text-left text-text">Access Ends</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-text-light">
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Course (with refund)</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Immediately upon cancellation</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Course (without refund)</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Access remains indefinitely</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Event booking</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Immediately (removed from attendee list)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Monthly subscription</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">End of current billing month</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-text/10">
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Annual subscription</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">End of current billing year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Account closure</td>
                  <td class="py-sm px-md">Immediately (30-day reactivation period)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6.3 Data Retention</h3>
          <p>
            What happens to your data:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Course progress:</strong> Kept for 90 days if refunded (in case of reinstatement)</li>
            <li><strong>Certificates:</strong> Revoked immediately if refund issued</li>
            <li><strong>Account data:</strong> Retained per Privacy Policy (see data retention section)</li>
            <li><strong>Payment records:</strong> Kept for 7 years (legal/tax requirements)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6.4 Email Communications</h3>
          <p>
            After cancellation:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li><strong>Transactional emails:</strong> Will stop (no more course notifications)</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing emails:</strong> You may still receive unless you unsubscribe</li>
            <li><strong>Account emails:</strong> Important account notices may still be sent</li>
            <li><strong>Unsubscribe:</strong> Use unsubscribe link in any email or Account Settings</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6.5 Refund Processing</h3>
          <p>
            If eligible for refund:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-lg space-y-xs">
            <li>See our <a href="/refund-policy" class="text-primary hover:underline">Refund Policy</a> for details</li>
            <li>Typically processed within 5-7 business days</li>
            <li>Refund goes to original payment method</li>
            <li>You'll receive confirmation when refund is issued</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 7 -->
      <section id="reinstatement" class="mb-2xl scroll-mt-lg">
        <h2 class="mb-lg text-2xl font-bold text-text">7. Reinstatement</h2>
        <div class="space-y-md text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">7.1 Reactivating Cancelled Items</h3>
          <p>
            If you change your mind:
          </p>
